# Patch 0015 — Per-workspace bookmarks + history attribution (ADR 0005).
#
# Completes ROADMAP Phase 2's isolation item per ADR 0005: bookmarks
# isolate, history attributes, passwords stay global (user decision).
#
# BOOKMARKS: Zen already ships the whole isolation mechanism — a
# zen_bookmarks_workspaces side table, star-panel Workspaces checkboxes,
# change-tracking for sync, and toolbar/menu filtering via
# isBookmarkInAnotherWorkspace(). Kavacha adds the missing convenience:
# with kavacha.workspaces.auto-assign-bookmarks on (Settings > Tab
# Management > workspaces group; default OFF), a user-created bookmark is
# assigned to the active space automatically. The write path mirrors
# PlacesUIUtils.updateBookmarkWorkspaces exactly (same table + changes row
# + moz_meta timestamp + workspace-bookmarks-updated notification), so
# Zen's cache refresh, filtering, and sync treat it like a manual
# assignment. Sync-/import-/restore-created bookmarks are never
# auto-assigned (source check), nor are tag "bookmarks" or bookmarks made
# from private windows.
#
# HISTORY: attribution, deliberately NOT isolation (hiding rows in a
# shared, synced places.sqlite would be privacy theater). A new
# kavacha_history_workspaces side table records (url, visit_time,
# workspace_uuid) per top-level http(s) navigation. Attribution happens at
# the TAB layer — a per-window tabs-progress listener reads the navigating
# tab's zen-workspace-id — because Places visit events carry no tab
# reference; this stays correct for background-tab loads. Private windows,
# same-document navigations, and space-less tabs (essentials) are skipped.
# Rows are batched (5s / 100 entries) and flushed on quit.
#
# First surface: universal search history results carry the badge of the
# space they were last visited in (the 0012 result contract already
# renders workspaceId badges).
#
# Marionette-verified: visits record with the correct space and resolve
# via latestWorkspaceForUrls; pref-off creates no assignment; pref-on
# assigns to the active space, the bookmark stays visible there and Zen's
# own filter hides it after switching spaces; history results in Search
# Everything show their space badge. Applies on top of 0014.
